  "prompt": "What are some cool Java tricks?",
  "response": "Here are some cool Java tricks and techniques:\n\n1. Null-Safe Operations\n```java\n// Elvis operator (Java 8+)\nString result = optionalString != null ? optionalString : \"Default\";\n// Or more concisely\nString result = Optional.ofNullable(optionalString).orElse(\"Default\");\n```\n\n2. Stream Manipulation\n```java\n// Filtering and transforming lists\nList<String> filtered = names.stream()\n    .filter(name -> name.startsWith(\"A\"))\n    .map(String::toUpperCase)\n    .collect(Collectors.toList());\n```\n\n3. Swap Without Temp Variable\n```java\na = a ^ b;\nb = a ^ b;\na = a ^ b;\n```\n\n4. Quick Array Initialization\n```java\nList<Integer> numbers = Arrays.asList(1, 2, 3, 4, 5);\n```\n\n5. Inline Conditional\n```java\nint max = (a > b) ? a : b;\n```\n\n6. Multi-Catch Exception Handling\n```java\ntry {\n    // Some code\n} catch (IOException | SQLException ex) {\n    // Handle multiple exception types\n}\n```\n\n7. Default Methods in Interfaces (Java 8+)\n```java\ninterface MyInterface {\n    default void defaultMethod() {\n        System.out.println(\"Default implementation\");\n    }\n}\n```\n\n8. Method References\n```java\nlist.forEach(System.out::println);\n```\n\n9. String Joining\n```java\nString joined = String.join(\", \", \"Apple\", \"Banana\", \"Cherry\");\n```\n\n10. Immutable List Creation\n```java\nList<String> immutableList = List.of(\"A\", \"B\", \"C\");\n```\n\n11. Compact Constructor (Java 14+)\n```java\npublic record Person(String name, int age) {\n    public Person {\n        Objects.requireNonNull(name);\n        if (age < 0) throw new IllegalArgumentException();\n    }\n}\n```\n\n12. Smart Type Inference (Java 10+)\n```java\nvar list = new ArrayList<String>();\n```\n\n13. Switch Expressions (Java 14+)\n```java\nint days = switch (month) {\n    case FEBRUARY -> 28;\n    case APRIL, JUNE, SEPTEMBER, NOVEMBER -> 30;\n    case JANUARY, MARCH, MAY, JULY, AUGUST, OCTOBER, DECEMBER -> 31;\n    default -> throw new IllegalArgumentException(\"Invalid month\");\n};\n```\n\n14. Optional Chaining\n```java\nString value = Optional.ofNullable(object)\n    .map(Object::toString)\n    .orElse(\"Default\");\n```\n\n15. Repeat String\n```java\nString repeated = \"A\".repeat(5); // \"AAAAA\"\n```\n\nBonus Performance Tip:\n```java\n// Use StringBuilder for string concatenation in loops\nStringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();\nfor (String s : strings) {\n    sb.append(s);\n}\nString result = sb.toString();\n```\n\nThese tricks can make your Java code more concise, readable, and sometimes more efficient. Remember that while these are cool, always prioritize code readability and maintainability.",
